{% extends "base.html.twig" %}

{% block title %}Upload a new item set{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
    <h2>Itemset to upload</h2>
    {% if error is defined %}
        <div class="alert alert-danger alert-dismissible" role="alert">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="alert" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>
            {{ error }}
        </div>
    {% endif %}
    <form action="{{ url('itemset', 'upload') }}" method="post" enctype="multipart/form-data">
        Uploading an item set, give you the full access to the RIOT Item Set API but not the website data as champion or comments.
        <div class="form-group">
            <label for="itemset">Item set</label>
            <input type="file" id="itemset" name="itemset" accept=".json">
            <p class="help-block">Maximum 50ko.</p>
        </div>
        <p class="help-block">PS : You can export your item set create in launcher.
        Load a game with the champion and map that has the specified item set. (custom works)
        <br>Access to <code>League of Legends\Config\Champions\{championKey}\Recommended\</code>
        and you will find an file name riot[...].json, you have just to upload this file (you can edit it if you want)!
        </p>
    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-default">Submit</button>
    </form>
{% endblock %}